blunder due to} 14... Rg8) 10... Nb6 11. Nh5 {If Black closes the queenside
after a3, ...c4, the best square for White's knight clearly is on h5.} 11... Bd7
12. Qg4 $16 {and the hit on g7 is extremely unpleasant as} 12... Rg8 {drops an
exchange after} 13. Nf6+ $1) 4... Bb4 (4... c5 {is not much more attractive here
than it was one move earlier. We force matters with} 5. dxc5 (5. Nf3 {is the
