in full control so naturally Black tries to counter with immediate strike in the
center.} 10... c5 (10... Re8 11. O-O $1 $16 { Now the only thing White needs to
do is to play Ne5 (or remove the queen from the e-file so that there are no
discovered attacks by the e8-rook) and he might as well get it in because Bf5
fails to the intermediate Bxf6 move which destroys Black's pawn structure and
weakens his king.}) 11. dxc5 { Unfortunately White's hands will get a bit dirty
in this line, but eventually he will emerge with the better position.}
